WEBVTT

00:09.954 --> 00:11.623
[engine shuts off]

00:13.561 --> 00:16.399
Hey, dude, I don't remember
the password. Let me in.

00:16.432 --> 00:17.669
I think someone's following me.

00:17.702 --> 00:19.439
Who?

00:19.472 --> 00:21.176
Get in here.
It's the doc crew.

00:21.209 --> 00:22.512
[sighs]

00:23.480 --> 00:24.617
You, too. Come on.

00:24.650 --> 00:26.186
When I ran away from Nandor,

00:26.219 --> 00:27.421
I didn't really know
where to go.

00:27.454 --> 00:30.294
[Nandor]
Guillermo!

00:30.327 --> 00:33.801
[Guillermo]
So I just flew
for hours and hours.

00:33.834 --> 00:35.404
Which was a little cool because

00:35.437 --> 00:37.208
that was the longest
I've ever stayed a bat.

00:37.241 --> 00:38.511
But also not cool

00:38.544 --> 00:40.214
because I knew Nandor was trying

00:40.247 --> 00:41.651
to track me down to kill me.

00:41.684 --> 00:43.788
Eventually, I just went
to Derek because...

00:43.821 --> 00:45.124
I had no one else to turn to.

00:45.157 --> 00:47.261
I've just been laying low,

00:47.294 --> 00:49.398
hiding for who knows how long.

00:50.768 --> 00:53.407
I wish they had Bravo here.

00:53.440 --> 00:55.545
["You're Dead"
by Norma Tanega playing]

00:55.578 --> 00:58.150
♪ Don't sing if you want
to live long ♪

00:58.183 --> 01:00.555
♪ They have no use
for your song ♪

01:00.588 --> 01:03.293
♪ You're dead, you're dead,
you're dead ♪

01:03.326 --> 01:06.232
♪ You're dead
and out of this world ♪

01:07.635 --> 01:10.675
♪ Now your hope and compassion
is gone ♪

01:10.708 --> 01:13.480
♪ You sold out your dream
to the world ♪

01:13.514 --> 01:15.752
♪ Stay dead, stay dead,
stay dead ♪

01:15.785 --> 01:17.856
♪ You're dead
and out of this world. ♪

01:17.889 --> 01:20.360
♪ ♪

01:27.942 --> 01:29.713
[door closes]

01:29.746 --> 01:31.282
I think there was a van
tailing me, they may have been

01:31.315 --> 01:32.284
-tailing you, too.
-Derek, that was them.

01:32.317 --> 01:33.921
Whoa.

01:33.954 --> 01:35.725
-You guys are good. Respect.
-Derek, just promise me

01:35.758 --> 01:37.562
you haven't told anyone else
that I'm here.

01:37.595 --> 01:39.499
Guillermo, who would I tell?
Literally. My neighbor Chad?

01:39.533 --> 01:41.469
Because... yes, actually,
I did tell Chad.

01:41.503 --> 01:42.839
This is serious, okay?

01:42.872 --> 01:44.308
My master is actively
trying to kill me.

01:44.341 --> 01:45.712
Did you bring my meat?

01:45.745 --> 01:47.649
Yes, burgers, extra rare,
just like you asked.

01:47.682 --> 01:49.820
I tried hypnosis on the cashier
so I could get them for free.

01:49.853 --> 01:51.524
Turns out, I'm bad at it.

01:51.557 --> 01:52.826
So, um,
I don't know if you use Venmo

01:52.859 --> 01:53.928
or maybe you're a Zelle guy...

01:53.961 --> 01:56.399
[retches]
These are not raw.

01:56.432 --> 01:58.303
I can taste that they've
kissed the grill, Derek.

01:58.336 --> 01:59.839
-[stammering]
-[knocking]

02:06.954 --> 02:08.691
-Sup, bitch?
-What the hell
are you doing here?

02:08.724 --> 02:10.227
Did anyone see you? Get inside.

02:10.260 --> 02:11.396
No, and it wouldn't
matter if they did

02:11.429 --> 02:13.935
because, hello,
I'm in disguise.

02:13.968 --> 02:15.170
Stop dancing, get inside.

02:15.203 --> 02:16.607
How did you find me?

02:16.640 --> 02:18.343
Your friend Derek told me
where you were hiding.

02:18.376 --> 02:19.613
[old-timey detective voice]
I paid him a little visit

02:19.646 --> 02:21.483
earlier today, see?

02:21.517 --> 02:22.719
So, that was you.

02:22.752 --> 02:24.288
-[laughs]
-Who did you think it was?

02:24.321 --> 02:26.359
She told me her name
was Detective Policeman.

02:26.392 --> 02:28.330
-[Nadja] That's funny.
-I'm gonna need you
to do me a favor, buddy.

02:28.363 --> 02:32.672
Can you go to the market and
get me some raw, raw meat

02:32.705 --> 02:34.610
and make sure you don't
tell anyone where I'm at.

02:34.643 --> 02:35.845
-Can you do that?
-Can do, can do.

02:35.878 --> 02:37.549
-Thank you, buddy.
-Okay, great.

02:37.582 --> 02:38.785
-Okay. Thanks so much.
-See you guys in a minute.

02:38.818 --> 02:40.522
Idiot.

02:40.555 --> 02:42.893
Guillermo. Sit.

02:42.926 --> 02:46.466
You simply cannot talk
to the vampire who turned you

02:46.499 --> 02:48.303
with such disrespect.

02:48.336 --> 02:50.340
That is a sacred relationship.

02:50.373 --> 02:51.844
You have to protect him.

02:51.877 --> 02:53.815
Like we protect the Baron
and the Sire.

02:53.848 --> 02:56.453
If anything was to happen
to that stupid man,

02:56.486 --> 02:58.958
the effects for you, my friend,
would be catastrophic.

02:58.991 --> 03:00.762
-Yes.
-[blows raspberry]

03:00.795 --> 03:02.599
I'm sorry, I shouldn't have
spoken to Derek like that.

03:02.632 --> 03:04.736
I'm just a little bit on edge
with the whole, you know--

03:04.769 --> 03:06.306
Nandor trying to kill you thing.

03:06.339 --> 03:08.511
-Awkward. [laughs]
-Which, by the way, um...

03:08.544 --> 03:09.713
Any progress on that end?

03:09.746 --> 03:11.817
Uh, yeah, um, a little.

03:11.850 --> 03:12.819
-You talked to him?
-Yeah.

03:12.852 --> 03:14.255
-Yeah?
-Yeah.

03:14.288 --> 03:15.390
What'd he say?

03:15.423 --> 03:17.495
-[screaming]
-Nandor, come on.

03:17.529 --> 03:18.831
I'm gonna murder him!

03:19.866 --> 03:21.504
Maybe if I write him a letter...

03:21.537 --> 03:24.242
Yeah, like if you wrote him
a suicide note,

03:24.275 --> 03:25.879
and actually followed through
on it,

03:25.912 --> 03:28.751
then that would
probably cool him down.

03:28.784 --> 03:31.824
-[faint moaning]
-[springs creaking]

03:31.857 --> 03:34.596
Wow. They're really
going at it, aren't they?

03:34.629 --> 03:35.732
[exhales]

03:35.765 --> 03:37.936
[sighs] Why did I do this?

03:37.969 --> 03:39.807
Look, relationships evolve.

03:39.840 --> 03:41.744
Like me and those Antipaxon
people who work at the diner.

03:41.777 --> 03:45.518
At first, I was just using them
to get rid of my hex.

03:45.551 --> 03:47.454
But then it turned out...

03:47.487 --> 03:49.560
I really like hanging out
with those guys.

03:49.593 --> 03:51.296
-[loud moaning]
-I know you didn't mean...

03:51.329 --> 03:52.699
[clears throat]
I know you didn't mean

03:52.732 --> 03:54.068
for things to turn out this way,

03:54.101 --> 03:56.005
-[loud moaning]
-but I think it's time

03:56.038 --> 03:57.441
you need to accept--
You know what?

03:57.474 --> 03:59.278
Hang on,
I cannot take this anymore!

03:59.311 --> 04:00.748
[man]
Yeah!

04:00.781 --> 04:02.418
-[springs creaking wildly]
-[door crashes open]

04:02.451 --> 04:04.489
-It's hard, you know.
-[woman moaning loudly]

04:04.523 --> 04:05.925
-[indistinct conversation]
-To know that
you've done something,

04:05.958 --> 04:08.664
that you messed up
but you can't...

04:08.697 --> 04:10.802
-[moaning resumes]
-...fix it and...

04:10.835 --> 04:13.039
-[Nadja moaning]
-And she's joined them.

04:13.072 --> 04:14.510
-[moaning]
-[thudding]

04:14.543 --> 04:18.316
[Nandor]
Night after night, I hunt.

04:18.349 --> 04:22.692
I cannot rest until Guillermo
has taken his last breath

04:22.725 --> 04:25.632
and I feel his bones
crunch under my boots.

04:25.665 --> 04:27.736
So I've been watching
the one place

04:27.769 --> 04:30.909
I know he will
return to eventually...

04:30.942 --> 04:32.979
Panera Bread.

04:33.012 --> 04:34.983
I've got you now.

04:35.016 --> 04:36.720
He can run,

04:36.753 --> 04:38.524
but he cannot run far.

04:38.557 --> 04:40.661
Because he has very short legs.

04:43.099 --> 04:45.838
-[gasps]
-Guillermo, now you will die.

04:45.871 --> 04:48.043
-I-I didn't do anything.
-[roaring]

04:48.076 --> 04:51.784
Those that betray me will pay
the ultimate price, Guillermo.

04:51.817 --> 04:53.119
And this disguise

04:53.152 --> 04:54.823
that has slightly altered
your appearance

04:54.856 --> 04:56.125
does not fool me.

04:56.158 --> 04:57.862
I'm not Guillermo!
I'm not Guillermo!

04:57.895 --> 05:00.067
I'm Patton Oswalt. I'm an actor.

05:00.100 --> 05:02.037
-Patton Oswalt?
-Yeah.

05:02.070 --> 05:03.507
-An actor?
-Yes!

05:03.540 --> 05:04.877
What would I know you from?

05:04.910 --> 05:06.680
-I was in Ratatouille.
-Is that a movie?

05:06.713 --> 05:08.584
It's... It was animated.

05:08.617 --> 05:09.786
I was the voice of a rat.

05:09.819 --> 05:12.091
-I prefer live action.
-Uh...

05:12.124 --> 05:13.694
Do you know John Slattery?

05:13.727 --> 05:15.531
I don't know him personally,
I know of him.

05:15.564 --> 05:17.535
-He seems really cool.
-He is.

05:17.568 --> 05:20.040
Yes, I-I'm gonna pass out...

05:20.073 --> 05:21.543
[groans]

05:21.576 --> 05:23.648
[coughing, gasping]

05:23.681 --> 05:24.917
Oh...

05:24.950 --> 05:27.154
My apologies, Patton Oswalt.

05:27.187 --> 05:29.458
You are respectful,
unlike Guillermo.

05:29.491 --> 05:30.962
I have been lying
in wait for him

05:30.995 --> 05:32.899
on the top of
that building there.

05:32.932 --> 05:34.035
It's only a matter of time

05:34.068 --> 05:36.072
before he returns
to Panera Bread,

05:36.105 --> 05:38.410
like a gazelle
to his watering hole.

05:38.443 --> 05:41.850
And when he does, I will strike.

05:41.883 --> 05:43.921
Are you sure it's
that Panera Bread?

05:43.954 --> 05:45.592
-What do you mean?
-There's a lot of Panera Breads.

05:45.625 --> 05:47.562
They're... They're all
over the city.

05:47.595 --> 05:48.630
Shit.

05:52.939 --> 05:54.576
-[knocking]
-Who is it?
-[Colin] Gigi?

05:54.609 --> 05:56.580
-Hello.
-What are you doing here?

05:56.613 --> 05:58.149
-How did you find me?
-Oh, I just...

05:58.182 --> 06:01.624
took a map of Staten Island
and laid it over a grid

06:01.657 --> 06:03.159
and looked for any motel
that shared a square

06:03.192 --> 06:05.865
with an Arby's, a party store
or a sweater shop.

06:05.898 --> 06:07.736
Well, I'm not near
any of those things.

06:07.769 --> 06:09.773
Yeah, I know,
so I just asked Nadja.

06:09.806 --> 06:11.977
Great. What do you want?

06:12.010 --> 06:14.148
First off, I just want
to wish you good luck.

06:14.181 --> 06:17.154
You're a nice enough guy
caught in a bad sitch.

06:17.187 --> 06:20.127
I-I don't think any of us were
hoping for this outcome for you.

06:20.160 --> 06:21.864
-[briefcase unlocks]
-Thank you.

06:21.897 --> 06:26.005
Secondly, I am here to conduct
your exit interview,

06:26.038 --> 06:28.143
from your job as a familiar.

06:28.176 --> 06:30.748
And also your life, so...

06:30.781 --> 06:34.155
Have a seat. I don't want to
take up too much of your time,

06:34.188 --> 06:36.894
I know it's valuable. [chuckles]

06:36.927 --> 06:39.498
Because
there's so little of it left.

06:39.532 --> 06:40.702
-Okay.
-[clicks]

06:40.735 --> 06:44.208
Familiar exit interview,
10:47 p.m.,

06:44.241 --> 06:47.014
Colin Robinson
conducting interview.

06:47.047 --> 06:48.551
Um, Mr. de la "Cruzz,"

06:48.584 --> 06:51.890
what's prompting you
to leave your job?

06:51.923 --> 06:53.561
Nandor trying to kill me.

06:53.594 --> 06:56.800
And... what was your salary
as a familiar?

06:56.833 --> 06:58.537
Oh, I don't get paid.

06:58.570 --> 07:01.643
[chuckles] No, but honestly,
for this to work,

07:01.676 --> 07:03.681
I kind of need
a ballpark figure.

07:03.714 --> 07:05.183
$500, $550 a week?

07:05.216 --> 07:06.787
-I don't get paid.
-Uh-huh.

07:06.820 --> 07:08.557
And do you think
we can get away with

07:08.590 --> 07:10.528
not paying the next person?

07:10.561 --> 07:12.799
Okay. This interview's over.

07:12.832 --> 07:15.972
Interview concluded by subject

07:16.005 --> 07:19.713
who was cooperative
and at times almost articulate.

07:19.746 --> 07:21.049
-[recorder clicks]
-Okay, thank you.

07:21.082 --> 07:23.086
This is just from me.

07:23.119 --> 07:25.525
It was nice having you
in the house.

07:25.558 --> 07:26.960
Thanks, Colin.

07:26.993 --> 07:30.601
"Jay Sturkel, Quarter Four
Sales Leader, 1977."

07:30.634 --> 07:34.509
I got it at estate sale,
but y-you get the drift.

07:35.845 --> 07:37.915
-Congratulations.
-Thank you.

07:39.017 --> 07:42.726
I think what bugs me the most

07:42.759 --> 07:44.896
is that I have given
Guillermo my friendship.

07:44.929 --> 07:47.836
This is a gift
I do not give to just anyone.

07:47.869 --> 07:51.543
Uh, you know, friendship
has to be... earned.

07:51.576 --> 07:53.113
How is your, um...

07:53.146 --> 07:54.616
-Turkey Bacon Bravo.
-Yes.

07:54.649 --> 07:56.018
It is, it's good.

07:56.051 --> 07:57.221
And I usually get
the bread bowls here--

07:57.254 --> 07:58.958
I think what it is

07:58.991 --> 08:02.063
is that I thought Guillermo
had earned it.

08:03.801 --> 08:06.707
You are a good listener,
Patton Oswalt.

08:06.740 --> 08:08.309
You know, it's funny
because something like this

08:08.342 --> 08:10.848
happened with me a couple years
ago with my manager, we--

08:10.881 --> 08:12.986
-Shh. Just listen.
-Oh... [grunts]

08:13.019 --> 08:15.290
We are not talking
about you right now,

08:15.323 --> 08:17.027
are we, Patton Oswalt?

08:17.060 --> 08:18.864
-No, we're not.
-Mm.

08:18.897 --> 08:21.035
-So, go on.
-Thank you.

08:22.605 --> 08:25.711
[knocking]

08:27.782 --> 08:29.586
Who is it?

08:29.619 --> 08:31.255
[Laszlo]
Housekeeping.

08:31.288 --> 08:33.259
-I should ask how you
found out where--
-Shh, shh.

08:33.292 --> 08:34.294
What?

08:35.798 --> 08:38.002
I'm guessing you're content
with your...

08:38.035 --> 08:39.773
toilet paper situation?

08:39.806 --> 08:41.209
Yes, thank you.

08:41.242 --> 08:43.012
All right.

08:43.045 --> 08:44.749
Then I will...

08:44.782 --> 08:47.354
leave you to watch
the television for the evening.

08:47.387 --> 08:50.160
And I will say... goodbye.

08:50.193 --> 08:51.897
-[quietly] Sit down.
-What's going on?

08:51.930 --> 08:54.870
I must apologize, Gizmo,
I feel like I've let you down.

08:54.903 --> 08:56.205
All those science experiments,

08:56.238 --> 08:57.876
they were nothing
but a blind alley.

08:57.909 --> 08:59.679
Laszlo, you tried your best.

08:59.712 --> 09:01.282
No, there's been something I...

09:01.315 --> 09:02.886
You-you should probably
put something on

09:02.919 --> 09:04.288
that's a bit louder than this.

09:04.321 --> 09:06.292
Otherwise, it won't
drown our voices out.

09:06.325 --> 09:08.029
-[airplanes whirring]
-That's better.

09:08.062 --> 09:11.169
I've known you since
you were a young familiar.

09:11.202 --> 09:13.039
And I may have been hard
on you in the past,

09:13.072 --> 09:15.177
-and, uh...
-[gunfire on TV]

09:15.210 --> 09:16.780
Could you put something that...

09:16.813 --> 09:18.784
is as loud but less percussive?

09:18.817 --> 09:20.253
-[engines roaring]
-Sport, yes, that's better.

09:20.286 --> 09:22.224
And I say,
does that thing have any...

09:22.257 --> 09:24.629
programs of the adult variety?

09:25.698 --> 09:27.201
Uh, I suppose, yeah.

09:27.234 --> 09:29.706
-[giggling]
-[Laszlo gasps]
-There you go.

09:29.739 --> 09:31.944
[clears throat] You were saying?

09:31.977 --> 09:33.046
Sorry?

09:33.079 --> 09:34.315
-You were saying?
-Yes.

09:34.348 --> 09:35.918
I was saying...

09:35.951 --> 09:38.657
I've known you since you were...

09:38.690 --> 09:40.327
-a young fa...
-[moaning on TV]

09:40.360 --> 09:42.064
What do you think
they're gonna do?

09:42.097 --> 09:43.667
-Yeah, Laszlo--
-Yes, yes,

09:43.700 --> 09:46.272
s-sorry, since you
were a young familiar.

09:46.305 --> 09:48.978
And, uh, I'm about
to tell you something now

09:49.011 --> 09:50.748
that I've never told
anyone else before.

09:50.781 --> 09:52.685
[moaning on TV]

09:52.718 --> 09:54.723
-L-Laszlo?
-Good grief.

09:54.756 --> 09:56.292
You were going
to tell me something

09:56.325 --> 09:58.363
-you never told
anyone before...?
-Shh. [laughs]

09:58.396 --> 10:00.000
You might have
to give me a minute.

10:00.033 --> 10:01.803
[Guillermo]
So, yeah, even Laszlo came by.

10:01.836 --> 10:03.339
If I would've known how...

10:03.372 --> 10:05.010
my last couple of days
would play out,

10:05.043 --> 10:06.713
how the last couple of months...

10:06.746 --> 10:08.216
I would've never asked
Derek to turn me.

10:08.249 --> 10:10.120
It's not that
I don't want to die,

10:10.153 --> 10:11.990
and trust me, I really,
really don't want to die,

10:12.023 --> 10:15.698
but I'm just more afraid
of losing the vampires.

10:15.731 --> 10:17.100
My friends.

10:17.133 --> 10:18.871
I always figured if I got
turned into a vampire

10:18.904 --> 10:21.442
that it would...
bring me closer to them.

10:21.475 --> 10:24.414
But it's just left me
feeling more alone than ever.

10:25.183 --> 10:27.989
Nandor, can I ask you
a question?

10:28.022 --> 10:29.759
Yes, Patton Oswalt.

10:29.792 --> 10:33.166
Your friendship with Guillermo
is very special, right?

10:33.199 --> 10:35.370
I thought it was.

10:35.403 --> 10:38.109
And I bet...

10:38.142 --> 10:40.748
killing a friend...

10:40.781 --> 10:42.184
would really hurt.

10:42.217 --> 10:44.388
I imagine it would be
one of the worst feelings

10:44.421 --> 10:46.158
a person could have.

10:46.191 --> 10:48.396
So, what if you...

10:48.429 --> 10:50.400
repair the friendship?

10:50.433 --> 10:52.137
-You repair it--
-So you're saying

10:52.170 --> 10:55.143
that I should not kill
my former friend?

10:55.176 --> 10:57.414
-Uh, yes, you-you--
-This is your suggestion?

10:57.447 --> 10:59.084
Well, you know, you rebuild--

10:59.117 --> 11:01.757
After hearing my tale
of deceit and betrayal?

11:01.790 --> 11:05.230
All that betray me
must be destroyed.

11:05.263 --> 11:07.234
-Wait, wait--
-Goodbye, Patton Oswalt.

11:07.267 --> 11:09.271
[screaming]

11:09.304 --> 11:10.775
[body thudding, crashing]

11:10.808 --> 11:12.044
-[loud thud]
-[sighs]

11:12.077 --> 11:14.247
He does make
a good point, though.

11:18.824 --> 11:20.894
-[on video] ...arm,
and a block of--
-[knocking loudly]

11:21.963 --> 11:23.366
Of course.

11:23.399 --> 11:27.775
Hi. I just came by
to pay you my condolences.

11:27.808 --> 11:31.182
"Sorry for your loss
of your life."

11:31.215 --> 11:33.754
Is there anyone who doesn't
know that I'm here?

11:33.787 --> 11:36.158
Well, I'm usually the last one
to know, so probably not.

11:36.191 --> 11:37.461
-Thank you.
-Yeah.

11:37.494 --> 11:39.131
And then I also brought
some friends

11:39.164 --> 11:40.768
who wanted to say goodbye.

11:40.801 --> 11:42.337
Hiya, Daddy.

11:42.370 --> 11:44.375
-Hey.
-Guide lady said
you're going off

11:44.408 --> 11:45.443
-to a big, beautiful...
-Hey, big guy.

11:45.476 --> 11:47.447
...farm in the sky.

11:47.480 --> 11:49.285
-Can we come?
-[Guillermo] Oh...

11:49.318 --> 11:50.888
-No, buddy.
-Aw.

11:50.921 --> 11:55.063
-There's no room at the farm.
-[sniffling]

11:55.096 --> 11:56.867
"In the death of a good man,

11:56.900 --> 11:59.004
eternity is seen looking
through time."

11:59.037 --> 12:00.841
Johann Wolfgang von Goethe.

12:00.874 --> 12:03.212
-[sobbing]
-Okay.

12:03.245 --> 12:04.949
-So-- Oh.
-[phone buzzing]

12:04.982 --> 12:06.052
Sorry.

12:06.085 --> 12:07.889
Hola, Ma.

12:07.922 --> 12:09.859
[Nandor]
Hello, Guillermo.

12:09.892 --> 12:11.897
I've been looking for you.

12:11.930 --> 12:13.567
Where are you?

12:13.600 --> 12:16.873
Oh, I'm right here having a nice
conversation with your mother.

12:16.906 --> 12:19.445
In her apartment.
Where she lives.

12:19.478 --> 12:21.015
My mother has nothing
to do with this.

12:21.048 --> 12:22.518
If you touch her, I swear...

12:24.087 --> 12:25.858
[Silvia speaking Spanish]

12:25.891 --> 12:27.562
Well, you know where I am.
Why don't you come over here

12:27.595 --> 12:29.365
and we can discuss
what happens next.

12:29.398 --> 12:30.500
[phone beeps]

12:30.534 --> 12:32.404
-I have to go.
-Bye, Daddy.

12:32.437 --> 12:34.041
Have you checked out already?
Or is it okay if we hang here?

12:34.074 --> 12:35.811
[Dog Guillermo]
He's not coming back.

12:37.548 --> 12:39.217
-Ah, come on, you stupid...
-[dings]

12:42.390 --> 12:44.529
-Get away from her.
-Guillermo.

12:44.562 --> 12:47.033
[speaking Spanish]

12:48.603 --> 12:49.839
I'll be back, okay?

12:49.872 --> 12:50.908
¿Cómo está, mijo?

12:50.941 --> 12:52.879
-Hey, Mami.
-Mwah.

12:52.912 --> 12:54.582
Don't be long, Sylvia.

12:54.615 --> 12:56.419
Still want to see
the photographs of Guillermo

12:56.452 --> 12:58.423
in this gotico phase.

12:58.456 --> 12:59.859
You can kill me if you want,

12:59.892 --> 13:00.995
but you leave her
out of this, okay?

13:01.028 --> 13:02.431
Oh, I know I could kill you.

13:02.464 --> 13:04.334
And you'd deserve it.

13:04.367 --> 13:07.407
[Guillermo panting]

13:09.545 --> 13:12.484
But I have decided not to.

13:12.518 --> 13:14.021
Yeah, well, I don't believe you.

13:14.054 --> 13:16.358
No, of course you don't.

13:16.391 --> 13:19.398
But something happened
recently and...

13:19.431 --> 13:21.202
it's made me change my mind.

13:21.235 --> 13:24.509
-Oh, yeah? What?
-My friend Patton Oswalt.

13:24.542 --> 13:27.515
He passed away quite suddenly.
And, um...

13:27.548 --> 13:31.021
it didn't feel good
losing a friend.

13:31.054 --> 13:33.059
How do I know
you're telling the truth?

13:33.092 --> 13:34.863
Because I give you
my word as a vampire.

13:34.896 --> 13:38.637
-[scoffs] Not good enough.
-Then I give you my word...

13:38.670 --> 13:40.206
as a warrior.

13:40.239 --> 13:42.578
-[hisses]
-[grunts]

13:43.947 --> 13:45.984
[speaking Persian]

13:46.986 --> 13:49.324
Translation:

13:49.357 --> 13:51.161
"If I'm lying...

13:52.698 --> 13:54.502
...then kill me now."

14:04.354 --> 14:05.490
Then it is settled.

14:05.524 --> 14:07.494
You'll come home with me, alive.

14:07.528 --> 14:08.630
Mami, no!

14:08.663 --> 14:11.302
[speaks Spanish]

14:11.335 --> 14:12.471
Wow, that worked.

14:12.505 --> 14:14.108
-Mm?
-Hmm?

14:14.141 --> 14:15.644
[owl hoots]

14:15.677 --> 14:17.147
We return with news.

14:17.180 --> 14:19.686
I no longer plan
to kill Guillermo.

14:19.719 --> 14:21.222
-Yay.
-[Nadja] Yay.

14:21.255 --> 14:22.592
He will live here
in this house, with us,

14:22.625 --> 14:24.394
-as an equal.
-[Laszlo laughs]

14:24.427 --> 14:26.098
As a vampire.

14:26.131 --> 14:29.138
-Boo.
-Where once we were four,
we are now five.

14:29.171 --> 14:30.541
I think your math is off.

14:30.574 --> 14:32.578
If I had known Gizmo was
going to stay with us,

14:32.611 --> 14:34.949
I would've said just kill him
and be done with it.

14:34.982 --> 14:36.586
[Colin]
Where is he going to sit?

14:36.619 --> 14:38.422
I-I'm not giving up my seat.
So where is he going to sit?

14:38.455 --> 14:42.030
Hold on a second. Gizmo cannot
fully become a vampire

14:42.063 --> 14:43.667
due to his Van Helsing blood.

14:43.700 --> 14:45.270
[Nandor]
Laszlo, Laszlo,

14:45.303 --> 14:47.407
with all your experiments
and your notetaking,

14:47.440 --> 14:49.679
and your weird-ass,
hybrid freaks,

14:49.712 --> 14:52.217
you never thought of
the simplest solution.

14:52.250 --> 14:55.724
-Which is?
-You never got Guillermo
to drink human blood.

14:55.757 --> 15:00.132
-Wait. Y-You never
thought of that?
-Shut up.

15:01.503 --> 15:03.640
-I don't think I can do this.
-You must.

15:03.673 --> 15:05.243
Or else you'll be
eternally frozen

15:05.276 --> 15:07.581
in this painful, unending limbo.
Now drink.

15:09.017 --> 15:10.453
Come on, Guillermo.

15:10.486 --> 15:12.224
-Drink, bitch.
-[Colin] Yeah, drink it, bitch.

15:12.257 --> 15:14.194
-[Laszlo] Yes.
-Drink it.
-[Nadja] Swallow it all.

15:14.227 --> 15:15.664
-Drink. Drink.
-[Nadja] Suck on it, baby.
Come on, drink!

15:15.697 --> 15:17.568
-Swallow it.
-Drink. Drink.
-Oi, drink.

15:17.601 --> 15:18.636
-Drink. Drink.
-[Nadja] Drink it.
Take it like a man.

15:20.373 --> 15:21.576
[gasps]

15:21.609 --> 15:23.246
[Laszlo]
Fangs.

15:23.279 --> 15:25.718
-[laughs]
-Wow
-Ah.

15:25.751 --> 15:27.354
I've never felt more alive.

15:27.387 --> 15:29.258
I really should've
thought of that.

15:29.291 --> 15:30.393
I'm a vampire. [laughs]

15:30.426 --> 15:31.696
I'm a vampire!

15:31.729 --> 15:35.170
-I'm a vampire!
-[Laszlo] Yahoo.

15:35.203 --> 15:36.238
Yep.

15:36.271 --> 15:37.742
-Nicely done.
-[laughs]

15:37.775 --> 15:41.081
[whooshing]

15:41.114 --> 15:44.154
-One sip of blood and he's
like Cornholio over here.
-[Laszlo laughs]

15:44.187 --> 15:45.356
Yes.

15:45.389 --> 15:46.526
-[Laszlo] He likes that.

15:46.559 --> 15:48.229
-[glass shatters]
-[Nadja] Ooh.

15:48.262 --> 15:51.202
Behold what I've become.

15:51.235 --> 15:53.306
Yes, yes, we've all been there.

15:53.339 --> 15:55.076
Why are we all
sitting on our asses?

15:55.109 --> 15:56.746
Let's do something!
What do we do next?

15:56.779 --> 15:57.782
Get a broom.

15:57.815 --> 15:59.752
Now, we hunt!

15:59.785 --> 16:02.558
-[cheering]
-[Nadja] I'm sorry,
Mommy needs to eat.

16:02.591 --> 16:04.294
-[Nandor] Hunt, hunt, hunt!
-[sighs]

16:04.327 --> 16:05.496
Hunt, hunt!

16:05.530 --> 16:07.266
FOMO.

16:10.439 --> 16:12.410
[Colin speaking quietly]

16:12.443 --> 16:14.014
Which reminds me,

16:14.047 --> 16:16.653
what's the fastest way
to become a millionaire?

16:16.686 --> 16:20.460
You start as a billionaire
and buy a winery.

16:20.493 --> 16:23.099
[chuckles] Just a little
wine humor for you.

16:23.132 --> 16:24.434
Oh. [belches]

16:24.467 --> 16:25.671
[Colin] Sommeliers are
a dying breed...

16:25.704 --> 16:28.309
Oh. I've eaten too much.
I feel sick.

16:28.342 --> 16:29.746
Go on, Guillermo.

16:29.779 --> 16:32.785
I bonked this one on the head
just for you.

16:32.818 --> 16:34.454
They're much easier
to drain and kill

16:34.487 --> 16:36.225
when they're not
wriggling around.

16:36.258 --> 16:38.296
Oh, no, I-I'm actually
not that hungry.

16:38.329 --> 16:41.068
Okay, well, FYI, if you leave
them hanging around too long

16:41.101 --> 16:44.742
when they're unconscious,
their blood, it loses its zing.

16:44.775 --> 16:47.047
[growling, slurping]

16:47.080 --> 16:49.351
[Guillermo]
I've never killed anyone before.

16:49.384 --> 16:52.157
I mean, I guess dozens
of vampires.

16:52.190 --> 16:53.760
And I did bring humans

16:53.793 --> 16:55.598
to the vampires
so they could kill them.

16:55.631 --> 16:56.833
And I've dismembered,

16:56.866 --> 16:58.704
like, a ton of dead bodies.

16:58.737 --> 17:01.275
But back at the restaurant,
that was a real living person.

17:01.308 --> 17:03.513
And when I leaned in to take...

17:03.546 --> 17:04.515
I could...

17:04.548 --> 17:07.220
smell their shampoo

17:07.253 --> 17:09.157
and all I kept thinking was

17:09.190 --> 17:10.561
this guy was at CVS

17:10.594 --> 17:12.497
just sniffing away
all these shampoos

17:12.531 --> 17:14.434
and says, "Eh, I think
I'll get this one

17:14.467 --> 17:16.573
because it reminds me of where
I used to go camping as a kid."

17:16.606 --> 17:18.209
[whimpers]

17:18.242 --> 17:20.113
I can't do this, I'm sorry.
Could we...

17:20.146 --> 17:22.316
-I can't--
-[audio cuts out]

17:25.189 --> 17:27.460
[door closes]

17:27.493 --> 17:29.531
[approaching footsteps]

17:34.542 --> 17:36.646
Just as I feared.

17:38.148 --> 17:41.555
Guillermo is not cut out
to be a vampire.

17:42.658 --> 17:45.129
I will fix.

17:48.503 --> 17:50.106
[whooshes]

17:50.139 --> 17:51.308
You summoned me?

17:51.341 --> 17:53.379
Yes, I wish for Guillermo--

17:53.412 --> 17:56.118
Eh, eh, you ran out
of wishes a long time ago.

17:56.151 --> 17:57.588
Have you just been
carrying me around?

17:57.621 --> 17:59.291
Maybe.

17:59.324 --> 18:00.728
-Yeah.
-[groans]

18:00.761 --> 18:02.230
Okay, well...

18:02.263 --> 18:04.535
Nice to see you again.
You can, uh...

18:04.568 --> 18:06.271
Can't I stretch
my legs a little?

18:06.304 --> 18:08.342
I wish I could help you,
but, uh...

18:08.375 --> 18:10.379
-That's very funny.
-Get in the fucking lamp.

18:14.855 --> 18:17.427
I didn't even know there
was a special ceremony for...

18:17.460 --> 18:19.565
Wait, what was the ceremony
called again?

18:19.598 --> 18:22.370
The Ceremony
of Vampiric Transmogrification.

18:22.403 --> 18:23.472
-Oh.
-Don't be nervous,

18:23.506 --> 18:24.742
we have all been through it.

18:24.775 --> 18:26.880
Well, is it scary?

18:26.913 --> 18:28.884
Nothing you cannot handle.

18:28.917 --> 18:31.589
The ancient ceremony will help
hasten you along your path.

18:31.622 --> 18:34.662
[ominous music playing]

18:34.695 --> 18:35.931
It is time.

18:35.964 --> 18:37.601
Are you ready?

18:37.634 --> 18:39.437
I am.

18:41.876 --> 18:43.479
♪ ♪

18:43.513 --> 18:44.949
Hey.

18:44.982 --> 18:46.653
Derek is here, too?

18:46.686 --> 18:48.957
Yes. Fucking guy.

18:48.990 --> 18:52.230
But ancient ritual dictates
that he must be present.

18:52.263 --> 18:54.702
-Come on.
-[Guillermo] Hey, everyone.

18:54.735 --> 18:56.472
Hello.

18:56.506 --> 18:57.641
-Derek.
-Hey.

18:57.674 --> 18:59.311
[music shuts off]

18:59.344 --> 19:00.848
-[Nandor clears throat]
-[stomps, bell tolls]

19:00.881 --> 19:04.555
Vampires all, gather we here
in the dark of night?

19:04.588 --> 19:05.824
[vampires]
We do.

19:05.857 --> 19:08.429
We have made of ourselves
a circle?

19:08.462 --> 19:10.266
-The circle--
-The circle unbroken.
-Unbroken.

19:10.299 --> 19:12.872
[Nandor]
We gather here
in a circle unbroken

19:12.905 --> 19:15.410
at the crossroads
between life and death.

19:15.443 --> 19:18.984
Guillermo de la Cruz,
are you prepared?

19:19.017 --> 19:20.621
I am.

19:20.654 --> 19:23.459
Guillermo de la Cruz,
are you of sound mind

19:23.492 --> 19:24.896
and strong of body?

19:24.929 --> 19:26.398
I am.

19:26.431 --> 19:27.701
A choice will be made.

19:27.734 --> 19:29.972
This choice can only
be made by you.

19:30.005 --> 19:33.279
We vampires here
are only witnesses.

19:33.312 --> 19:36.351
Mistress of Ceremony,
prepare the flames.

19:36.384 --> 19:37.821
[clears throat] That's me.

19:38.923 --> 19:40.694
Nicely done.

19:40.727 --> 19:44.702
Guillermo de la Cruz,
I will now ask you one question.

19:44.735 --> 19:47.608
The answer must come
from your heart.

19:47.641 --> 19:49.545
For this is the last time

19:49.578 --> 19:51.583
you get to make
this final choice.

19:51.616 --> 19:53.687
-Do I make myself clear?
-Mm-hmm.

19:53.720 --> 19:57.661
The question is:
Would you rather be a human...

19:59.430 --> 20:01.000
...or vampire?

20:09.685 --> 20:11.287
A human.

20:14.962 --> 20:16.566
As I predicted.

20:16.599 --> 20:17.868
It's not that I don't
want to be a vampire,

20:17.901 --> 20:19.337
-I really, really do.
-Sure.

20:19.370 --> 20:20.741
It's all the killing.

20:20.774 --> 20:22.443
You can spare us the details,
it's fine.

20:22.476 --> 20:24.615
You want to be a human,
there's no shame in that.

20:24.648 --> 20:26.051
-We're gonna make it happen.
-Wait, what?

20:26.084 --> 20:29.692
Mistress of Ceremony,
distribute the hoods.

20:29.725 --> 20:31.328
That's me again.

20:31.361 --> 20:34.434
-You're doing a great job.
-Thank you, Derek.

20:34.467 --> 20:36.038
-Can I get a smaller--
-They're unisex.

20:36.071 --> 20:37.808
-It's a one size fits all
situation? Okay.
-Yep. Mm-hmm.

20:37.841 --> 20:39.779
Do I get a hood, or...

20:39.812 --> 20:40.781
-[Nandor] Hurry it up.
-[Baron] I have one
for you, too.

20:40.814 --> 20:42.383
[Sire]
Thank you.

20:42.416 --> 20:45.657
We blind ourselves
that none may witness.

20:45.690 --> 20:47.460
Hoods on, everyone.

20:47.493 --> 20:50.066
♪ We blind ourselves ♪

20:50.099 --> 20:55.577
[together]
♪ That none may see. ♪

20:55.610 --> 20:58.315
[Nandor] Very nice.
Proceed to position two.

20:58.348 --> 20:59.819
[bell tolling]

20:59.852 --> 21:01.355
[Derek]
I'm sorry,
w-what's position two?

21:01.388 --> 21:02.791
Just as you are, Derek,
that's fine.

21:02.824 --> 21:05.564
-Wait, what?
-It is the only way, Guillermo.

21:05.597 --> 21:07.601
-W-Won't I die, too?
-No.

21:07.634 --> 21:09.805
You'll go back to how you were
when you were turned.

21:09.838 --> 21:12.410
You'll just get a month older
really quickly.

21:12.443 --> 21:13.813
There's got to be another way.

21:13.846 --> 21:15.751
There's no other way.

21:15.784 --> 21:17.921
It is the only way.

21:33.920 --> 21:35.389
[exhales]

21:38.495 --> 21:40.099
-I can't do this.
-[coughs] Knew it.

21:40.132 --> 21:42.036
[Derek]
I'm sorry, can't do what?
What am I missing?

21:42.069 --> 21:43.038
[Nandor]
Just keep that hood on, Derek.
You're doing great.

21:43.071 --> 21:44.040
[Derek]
Thank you.

21:44.073 --> 21:46.010
You want me to do it?

21:47.948 --> 21:50.119
-I don't know.
-I do.

21:50.152 --> 21:51.722
Give me that.

21:53.091 --> 21:55.731
[Derek grunts]

21:55.764 --> 21:58.837
[Nandor]
Guillermo, you okay?

21:58.870 --> 22:00.607
-[Colin] Whoa!
[Laszlo] Um...
-[Nandor] Oh, shit.

22:00.640 --> 22:02.443
[Guillermo]
Everything's kind of blurry.

22:02.476 --> 22:04.013
I think I need my old glasses.

22:05.617 --> 22:07.487
-Here.
-Thank you.

22:07.521 --> 22:08.957
Well, that was fun.

22:08.990 --> 22:10.594
Can we turn the regular lights
on now, please?

22:10.627 --> 22:12.865
Oh, sure. Can somebody
help me pick up all these

22:12.898 --> 22:15.002
hoods and robes?

22:15.035 --> 22:16.906
Eh, just leave them.
Garfield will pick 'em up later.

22:16.939 --> 22:20.112
I must say, the, uh,
the banners are a lovely touch.

22:20.145 --> 22:21.583
You know, I like them, too.

22:21.616 --> 22:22.851
What do they mean?

22:22.884 --> 22:24.622
I don't know,
to be honest, Baron.

22:24.655 --> 22:26.926
I just wanted something
that looked cool and creepy.

22:26.959 --> 22:28.462
Very nice, yes.

22:28.495 --> 22:30.132
[speaking vampiric language]

22:30.165 --> 22:32.504
We have a sitter waiting at
home, so we're gonna head out.

22:32.537 --> 22:34.107
-Good evening.
-Kalinychta.
-[Guide] Bye.

22:34.140 --> 22:36.613
[Nandor] Anyone up for
a game of parcheesi?

22:36.646 --> 22:38.082
[Nadja] Maybe a movie.

22:38.115 --> 22:39.518
-I'm zonked.
-[Colin] The Brothers McMullin?

22:39.551 --> 22:40.821
That wasn't even
a real ceremony, was it?

22:40.854 --> 22:42.558
No.

22:42.591 --> 22:45.631
I found the robes in a box
in the attic and, uh...

22:45.664 --> 22:48.034
the candles I think we got
from a Home Depot?

22:50.674 --> 22:52.578
I'm sorry, Guillermo.

22:52.611 --> 22:53.880
It was the only way
for you to figure out

22:53.913 --> 22:55.717
what you actually wanted.

22:55.750 --> 22:58.489
It was a horrible
and hard decision.

22:58.523 --> 23:00.058
I think you made
the right choice.

23:01.629 --> 23:03.198
I know.

23:03.231 --> 23:05.102
Now, if you wouldn't mind
clearing up Derek's corpse

23:05.135 --> 23:07.874
before sunrise,
that would be great.

23:14.521 --> 23:17.528
Its alright i"ll give you a hand.

23:17.561 --> 23:18.929
Thanks, Laszlo.

23:20.199 --> 23:22.871
♪ ♪

23:26.044 --> 23:28.182
-You take the bag,
I'll take Derek.
-Okay.

23:28.215 --> 23:30.486
Come on, old chap.
You better get the door.

23:30.520 --> 23:31.622
[Guillermo]
Mr. Necromancer?

23:31.655 --> 23:33.058
[knocking]

23:34.661 --> 23:36.833
And you have the necessary
items required

23:36.866 --> 23:38.503
for the procedure to succeed?

23:38.536 --> 23:40.540
He means the cash.

23:40.573 --> 23:41.943
[Guillermo]
Yeah, it was almost all
the money I gave Derek

23:41.976 --> 23:43.913
to turn me into a vampire.

23:43.946 --> 23:46.853
He only spent like $270
on "vampire clothes"

23:46.886 --> 23:49.190
that he got from Hot Topic.

23:49.223 --> 23:52.196
You don't need to count it.
It's all there, necromancer.

23:52.229 --> 23:53.666
I should trust you

23:53.699 --> 23:55.504
when you when you show me
no respect for me

23:55.537 --> 23:57.541
or my beguiling powers?

23:57.574 --> 23:58.943
Respect? For a fraud?

23:58.976 --> 24:01.114
But you've seen
my methods succeed.

24:01.147 --> 24:03.853
I've seen your magic.
It has a fraudulent vibe.

24:03.886 --> 24:05.590
Okay, okay.
Boys, why don't we focus?

24:05.623 --> 24:07.894
[chanting]

24:10.099 --> 24:12.871
He's doing his scatting shit.

24:12.904 --> 24:15.744
-[chanting]
-[bell tolls]

24:15.777 --> 24:19.183
-[thunder crashing]
-[manic chanting]

24:22.791 --> 24:25.262
Yah! [spits]

24:25.295 --> 24:27.166
Get in, you dirty bastard!

24:27.199 --> 24:28.937
[gasps]

24:28.970 --> 24:30.139
[gurgling]

24:30.172 --> 24:31.274
Derek...

24:31.307 --> 24:33.613
[gasping]

24:33.646 --> 24:35.817
[raspy]
What's up, dude?

24:35.850 --> 24:37.688
All right. Begone with ya.

24:37.721 --> 24:39.224
He's all yours.

24:39.257 --> 24:41.696
